snippet.textDisplay: "Why do you use cable?"  -- I use cable internet ($15 per month for low end broadband) because my only other choices are both crappy service wise and expensive.   Due to where I live,  a few miles too far out from the phone line service center that my neighborhood is hooked up to,  my other choices are expensive ($70/month) satellite (which requires an expensive landline) or an expensive ($40/month) landline with a dial-up modem.     This way I can use a NetDuo for phone ($30/year) and since I rarely watch TV,  my costs are minimal.  And no,  I prefer not to use cell phones,  they are way too expensive.
